Class Date

java.lang.Object
clinic.cs213project3.model.util.Date
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Date>
public class Date extends Object implements Comparable<Date>
This is the object structure for an appointment's date. Each date object stores the day, month, and year stored as integers.
Author:
Aarush Desai, Rohan Vuppunuthula

    • Date

      public Date(int year, int month, int day)
      Constructor creates a new date object. The year, day, and month are stored as integers.
      Parameters:
      year - The date's year as an integer.
      month - The date's month ranging from 0 to 11.
      day - The date's day as an integer.

  • Method Details

    • isThirtyOneDayMonth

      private boolean isThirtyOneDayMonth()
      Checks if a date's month contains exactly 31 days. Only January, March, May, July, August, October, and December have 31 days.
      Returns:
      True if the date's month has 31 days, else False.

    • isThirtyDayMonth

      private boolean isThirtyDayMonth()
      Checks if a date's month contains exactly 30 days. Only April, June, September, and November have 30 days.
      Returns:
      True if date's month has 30 days, else False.

    • isLeapYear

      private boolean isLeapYear()
      Checks if a date's year is a leap year.
      Returns:
      True if date's year is a leap year, else False.
